Professor Lam is pretty much a math god sent from heaven. He makes calculus easy to understand and writes crystal clear notes in lecture. He has a quirky personality which always seem to lighten up the mood in class. By far, he's my favorite prof at UofT. I'd trade my kidney for a brain like his.
